#Q4 How is data organized in each column? Is it properly organized?
Through the perspective of data analysis, the data is poorly organized as there are several categorical values, repetitive columns and some of the columns will not add any value in our analysis.

#Q5 Is data in the proper shape for further analysis? Though there is a lot of information through different variables, still the data is not in proper shape for further analysis.

The reasons are as follows: 1. company_name_id could have been a numeric id. 2. There are lot of missing values which needs to be imputed with suitable method. 3. The format of url is different throught the column. 4. Format of displaying full_time_employees is different throught the column. 5. In revenue_source multiple sources are given which needs to be standardized for analysis. 6. The menaing of some columns are hard to make out and thus a discription of variables is required. 7. There are a lot of unwanted characters. 8. The count in used_by_fte needs to be standardized.

Thus, there are lots of changes to be made before further analysis.

#Q6 How will you fix this dataset? There are several steps we can take, such as: 1. Imputing missing values by mean for numeric values and mode for categorical values. 2. Standardizing the values in columns with a particular format. 3. Normalizing the data. 4. Removing duplicate data. 5. Removing the outliers. 6. Finding the meaning for those variables which we do not understand.

For instance, we can form the dataset without duplicates like this:

Agencies %>% unique()
Companies %>% unique()

#Q4 What is the total traffic of vehicles on geolocations, (41.651861, -87.54501) and(41.66836, -87.620176) Total Traffice between these geolocations: 13600.

for(l in 1:1279){
  if(Total_Traffic[[l]][[15]]=="41.651861" && Total_Traffic[[l]][[16]]== "-87.54501"){a<-as.numeric(Total_Traffic[[l]][[13]])}
  if(Total_Traffic[[l]][[15]]=="41.66836" && Total_Traffic[[l]][[16]]== "-87.620176"){b<-as.numeric(Total_Traffic[[l]][[13]])}
}
Total_Traffic = a+b
print(Total_Traffic)
## [1] 13600
